    "It's a \"black box,\" to use a term first applied to computing by one of the founders of cybernetics (Ashby 1956: 86).",
    "There's a ghost in the machine.To compare how humans make meaning, we are going to take three \"walked\" sentences, illustrated here with images created by prompts served to the image generator, Leonardo AI (Figs. 456).",
    "In school, we have traditionally done some basic parsing of the meaning of sentences like these.",
    "There's a subject (he) and a predicate (his walking).",
    "There are nouns, pronouns that can point to a noun, a verb, and we can see that it's in the past tense."
